# Changelog — RavLight Core

Format: [Keep a Changelog](https://keepachangelog.com/en/1.0.0/)
Versioning: [Semantic Versioning](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html)

---

## [2.23.6] — 2026-07-21

### Added
- **Set up WiFi from the browser** — the web installer can now send WiFi credentials to the board over the same USB cable used for flashing (Improv), so a fresh board goes straight onto your network without hopping to its temporary access point. Boards whose serial port drives LEDs keep the access-point setup
- **RDM support (experimental)** — devices on a wired DMX line now answer RDM: a lighting console can discover the fixture, read its identity and firmware version, flash it to identify it, read its label and set its DMX start address. Wired DMX only for now — RDM over Art-Net/sACN is planned

## [2.23.5] — 2026-07-20

### Changed
- **Orion — Control start auto-fills** — when you set the Position start address (or change personality), the Control start address now updates automatically to sit right after the position channels, the same way the Veyron addresses do. You can still override it by hand

## [2.23.4] — 2026-07-20

### Added
- **MAC address in the Network section** — the device's MAC address is now shown in the Network panel and in the device Info popup, making it easy to identify a unit on your network or in your router

## [2.23.3] — 2026-07-20

### Changed
- **Update check works everywhere** — checking for a new firmware version no longer needs a secure (HTTPS) connection, so it now succeeds even on boards short on memory or running over WiFi (before, it could report "can't reach update server"). Firmware itself is still verified on install
- **Smaller firmware** — the build dropped ~90 KB, leaving more free space on 4 MB boards

### Fixed
- **Flash layout** — the two firmware slots are now the same size (they were mismatched), and the layout is unified across all boards. Adopting this needs a one-time USB flash; afterwards, future updates — including a possible platform upgrade — can be delivered over the air

## [2.23.2] — 2026-07-19

### Changed
- **Simpler, always-reliable updates** — "Check for updates" now offers a **download link** for the latest firmware instead of downloading it on the device. You save the file with your browser and flash it with "Upload firmware". The on-device download could fail on a unit that had been running for a long time (not enough contiguous memory for the secure transfer); the version check and the file upload work regardless of uptime or connection

## [2.23.1] — 2026-07-18

### Fixed
- **More reliable "check for updates"** — the online update check now retries a few times, so it succeeds more often on a device that has been running for a long time (previously it could report "can't reach update server" until the next reboot). Uploading a firmware file by hand was, and remains, always available

## [2.23.0] — 2026-07-17

### Added
- **Over-the-air updates** — the device can update its own firmware over the network. Click the **FW** badge in the header to open the Firmware panel: it checks for a newer version, shows what's new, and installs it with one tap — then reboots and confirms the new version is running, with automatic rollback if it fails to boot
- **Manual firmware update** — upload a firmware file straight from the Firmware panel. Works offline and with any build
- **Single-file firmware** — the web interface is now built into the firmware image, so an update (over the air or by USB) is a single file with no separate filesystem to flash
- **Failsafe update page** — a tiny always-available `/update` page to upload firmware even when the device is low on memory and the full interface won't load
- **Recovery over serial (USB)** — a minimal serial console for when the device is unreachable on the network: check status, reboot, set WiFi credentials, toggle ESP-NOW discovery, or factory-reset — no reflash needed

### Changed
- **Firmware panel** — the firmware version and updates moved out of Settings into a dedicated panel opened from the FW badge in the header
- **Orion visual setup** — the winch configuration is now a single always-visible panel with a stylized winch diagram: home is always position 0, travel is a positive distance, and the direction is implied by the homing direction — no more confusing signed limits. Jog, bypass limits, set-home, set-limit, live position, a cm/inch selector and the DMX reference are all in one place; the old multi-step setup wizard is gone
- **Faster page loading** — the interface now caches its files in the browser, so re-opening or reloading the page is near-instant instead of re-downloading everything each time; a new firmware automatically refreshes the cache
- **Smoother motorized fixtures** — the live StallGuard readout only updates while it's actually on screen, so a motorized rig like Orion now loads as quickly as an LED-only one
- **Save config button** — floats at the bottom of the page and stays visible while you scroll; sits quietly outlined and fills yellow on hover, matching the other buttons

### Fixed
- **Reliable web interface on motorized boards** — the motor no longer starves the web server, so the page loads and stays responsive while the winch is running
- **ESP-NOW discovery is now opt-in** — kept off by default so it can't starve the network stack on Ethernet boards; enable it from the Network settings when you need it

## [2.22.0] — 2026-07-12

### Added
- **Elyon performance** — big frame-rate gain on pixel rigs: the I2S LED backend now sizes its DMA cycle to the actual configured strip length instead of the maximum, lifting an 8×325-pixel Octa from ~22 to 60+ fps under a full Resolume load
- **Orion manual mode** — one switch disables every automatic safety (stall detection, DMX-loss watchdog, auto-rehome), leaving manual jog and set-home. The way onto a fixture that's already mounted and can't be calibrated on a bench
- **Orion auto-home at boot** — optionally take the current shaft position as home a moment after power-up, so direct-drive rigs (whose load drops when powered off) resume DMX cues without a manual home every time
- **Orion stall recovery options** — "keep home after stall" for self-locking worm-gear rigs (position survives, no forced re-home), and "drop & re-home" for direct-drive rigs (de-energise so the load settles, then re-home)
- **Orion stall sensitivity** — a Balanced/Aggressive/Tolerant selector that tunes how readily StallGuard trips, applied when the calibration sweep runs
- **Orion browser installer entry** — the whole project is now flashable and documented at [ravlight.com](https://ravlight.com)

### Changed
- **Orion setup wizard** — rebuilt one step at a time with progress dots and Prev/Next, and a manual-home-first flow so a loaded rig can be set up without relying on sensorless homing
- **Orion configuration page** — reorganized into clear sections (DMX, Motion, Homing, Jog & Travel, Stall detection, Setup); motor currents are shown read-only outside the wizard to avoid accidental changes; a jog speed selector (full / half / quarter) makes fine positioning easier
- **Orion motion limits** — speed, acceleration and jog values are capped to safe maximums; entering a higher value is clamped instead of silently losing motor steps

### Fixed
- **Orion stall detection reliability** — calibration now derives the correct StallGuard threshold (previously doubled, so homing tripped almost immediately), uses more of the travel for a tighter measurement, and detects genuine stalls that were previously missed
- **Orion E-STOP holds the load** — an emergency stop (or a stall) now keeps the motor energised so a suspended load stays put, instead of releasing it
- **Orion jog reliability** — jogging no longer false-trips a stall on release or on quick direction changes, and stays responsive at higher speeds without overshooting the travel limits
- **Elyon on QuinLED Octa** — device discovery and serial logging are off by default on this board, removing the radio interference and pin conflicts that caused brief freezes on the LED outputs under heavy ArtNet load

## [2.21.0] — 2026-06-29

### Added
- **Live DMX-source switch** — changing the DMX source from ArtNet to sACN, Built-in Effects, Wired DMX or Auto-Scene no longer needs a device restart. The save applies instantly and pixels pick up the new source on the next frame
- **Universal FPS counter** — the FPS display in the Info popup and on the Axon OLED now reflects the true source frame rate whether you're feeding the device via ArtNet, sACN, wired DMX input or the built-in effects engine, and works for single-universe or multi-universe rigs
- **Axon DMX OUT panel** — dedicated card on the Axon fixture page styled like the LED output cards. Shows live wire frame rate + current channel offset in the header; body has a 0–511 channel-offset input for slicing a big source universe across multiple daisy-chained nodes
- **Fixture-aware built-in effects** — each fixture now declares exactly which pixel channels the effects renderer may paint. Veyron in Solid/Rainbow/Chase/Twinkle no longer spills random RGB into the strobe or dim channels, so a "solid red" effect stays a solid red instead of also strobing at random
- **Veyron white + strobe sliders** — three new sliders on the Effects panel (visible only on Veyron): White accent (the 6 P9813 COB LEDs), Strobe RGB (strip strobe rate), Strobe White (accent strobe rate). Live-save like everything else on the panel

### Changed
- **Veyron saves apply live** — personality, RGBW/white/strobe start addresses and dim curves are all applied on the next frame instead of triggering a 10 s device restart
- **ArtPollReply** — the reply the device sends to network discovery polls now carries the actual firmware version (was always displayed as 0.0), a `RavLight <fixture>` long name, and marks the OEM slot as custom/unregistered instead of impersonating another vendor's OEM code
- **Ethernet link timeout** — devices with a self-generated PHY reference clock (Octa, QuinLED-ESP32-AE, XDMX v1.4) now wait up to 5 s for the link to come up at boot instead of 2 s. A slightly late-linking cable used to drop the device to WiFi for the whole session

### Fixed
- **Slave-mode transmit collision** — configuring a Veyron/Axon with DMX Wired input AND the DMX output flag on simultaneously used to make the device briefly transmit on the same wire it was reading, corrupting the upstream master's signal and freezing every downstream slave. The UI now hides the output toggle when input is set to Wired DMX, and the firmware forces the output off in that case regardless of stored config
- **DMX Monitor on Veyron** — universes shown on the DMX Monitor page were always zero when the source was an Art-Net 4 controller like Resolume (the sync-mode pool swap wasn't being applied on Veyron)
- **Glitch during source switch** — switching from ArtNet or sACN to Built-in Effects (or between the two network sources) used to leak residual packets from the previous source into the new one for ~50 ms, showing as a burst of stale colours before the new source took over. The receive callbacks are now gated by explicit runtime flags flipped low before tear-down

---

## [2.20.5] — 2026-06-22

### Added
- **Built-in effects engine** — five standalone effects (Solid, Rainbow, Chase, Fire, Twinkle) generate ArtDMX internally when DMX Source = "Built-in Effects". Useful for diagnostics, demos, and as a fallback when no ArtNet/sACN controller is on the network. Configurable colour / speed / intensity from the DMX tab. Enabled on every Elyon env and on Veyron; skipped on Orion (winch) and the bring-up test env
- **RGBW stride mode** — toggle in the Effects panel that switches the engine from a 3-byte (RGB) to a 4-byte (RGBW) pixel stride and extracts the common R∩G∩B component into the W channel. Pick white in the colour picker and on an SK6812/WS2814 strip only the W LED lights
- **Live preview** — effect / colour / speed / intensity now apply on the strip the instant you drag the slider or change the colour picker. No Save click, no restart. Save still bundles the full config for persistence
- **Restart only on structural changes (Elyon)** — saving the Elyon page no longer blanks the strip for ~3 seconds on every click. Brightness, gamma, colour order, grouping, DMX map and effects are all applied live; the driver only restarts when the protocol, pixel count, backend or clock partner actually changes

### Changed
- **Effects colour picker is RGB-native** — the picker now writes raw R/G/B instead of a hue index, so white, pastels and any picker-perfect colour are reachable. Solid/Chase/Twinkle take their brightness directly from the picker; the Intensity slider is hidden for those (it only affects Rainbow and Fire, which generate their own colours)
- **Chase / Twinkle background** — pure black (was a low-luminance grey wash that showed up on RGBW strips as a dim white background)
- **Chase span scales with the registered universe set** — was hard-coded to a 32-universe world, so on short strips the trail only crossed the visible window once every couple of minutes; now it scales so the head sweeps the actual rig length

### Fixed
- **Web UI cache invalidation** — text assets (HTML / JS / CSS) ship with no-cache headers so an OTA upgrade shows up on the next refresh. Static images keep a 1-hour cache
- **First-paint blank cards** — the dashboard loads its scripts serially instead of fanning out parallel fetches that overran the embedded web server on slower links; the fixture renderer is also guaranteed to be present before init() runs

---

## [2.20.4] — 2026-06-20

### Added
- **Art-Net 4 ArtSync support** — controllers that emit ArtSync packets (Resolume, MA3, Chamsys, ETC EOS over Art-Net, …) now drive frame-coherent rendering: every universe in a frame becomes visible atomically instead of trickling in as ArtDMX packets arrive. The universe pool is double-buffered internally; render reads the active half lock-free. Legacy controllers without sync (xLights, etc.) automatically fall back to the previous inline-apply behaviour
- **sACN Extended Synchronization** — same frame-coherent semantics for E1.31 controllers (grandMA3 onPC, ETC EOS, Chamsys, Hog OPC, …). Detected via VECTOR_E131_EXTENDED_SYNCHRONIZATION (framing vector 0x00000001) and routed through the same pool-swap mechanism as ArtSync
- **Per-output gamma correction (Elyon)** — new `gamma_x10` field per LED output: 10 = linear (default, backward compat), 22 = γ 2.2 (typical LED perceptual linearisation), range 10..30. Baked into the existing per-output 256-byte brightness LUT, so the per-pixel render cost remains a single table lookup
- **`/stats` runtime perf endpoint** — JSON snapshot of render FPS, average / peak frame time, mutex wait time, per-universe heap counters, ArtNet pps, ArtSync and sACN sync counts. `POST /stats/reset` zeroes the accumulators for clean A/B measurement
- **Elyon dual-core render task** — LED rendering runs on a dedicated FreeRTOS task pinned to Core 0, woken by xTaskNotifyGive or a 20 ms safety tick. Frees Core 1 (Arduino loop) from re-rendering on every iteration. Mutex hold time during render dropped from full-frame (~35 ms) to ~5 µs swap window

### Performance
Measured on QuinLED Octa under Resolume ArtNet load (8 × 325 px, 16 universes):
- Render-time tail latency `render_us_max`: 103 ms → 47 ms (-54%)
- Mutex contention `mutex_wait_max`: 2.85 ms → 874 µs (-69%)
- ArtNet packet ingestion: roughly doubled
- Minimum free heap: 85 KB → 91 KB (the per-universe double buffer adds 16 KB; the rest is recovered from less heap thrash)

Steady-state FPS is unchanged at ~28 — the hpwit `showPixels(WAIT)` blocking flush is the hard ceiling (matches sun-lightrig-led-controller's ~40 fps for 340 px on SPI). The wins live in coherency and consistency.

### Changed
- **Per-pixel brightness math replaced by precomputed LUT** (Elyon) — pulled the multiply-divide off the render hot path. Universe pointer caching added to the I2S branch (was per-pixel `getUniverseData()` linear scan), matching the RMT branch's behaviour. Also fixes a latent cross-universe-boundary bug in the I2S WS path
- **I2S DMA copy uses bulk memcpy** instead of a per-pixel `setPixel()` loop when source and device wire widths match (the common case). 4-8× faster than the function-call-per-pixel loop on aligned DMA buffers

---

## [2.20.3] — 2026-06-19

### Changed
- **I2S parallel LED backend is now the default for every Elyon env.** The `[ravlight].elyon_i2s_flag` toggle ships ON; flipping it back to empty rolls every Elyon env back to the RMT backend. Boards that don't use pixel LEDs (analog PWM Penta+, Penta Deca) are unaffected — the I2S init finds zero WS281x outputs and is a no-op
- **BLE module removed.** The on-device NimBLE provisioning never reached working state and is no longer planned: the mobile app will use UDP discovery + WiFi config over the existing web UI. Removes the NimBLE library from the build, the `RAVLIGHT_MODULE_BLE` guards from the source, and `src/ble_manager.*` from the tree. Drops ~5 s build time and ~50 KB of compiled code per env

---

## [2.20.2] — 2026-06-19

### Changed
- **Elyon I2S backend is now a build-time toggle, not a separate env.** Removed `quinled_octa_elyon_i2s` and `generic_esp32_test_elyon_i2s`; both are now produced by setting `elyon_i2s_flag` and `elyon_i2s_lib` in the `[ravlight]` section at the top of `platformio.ini`. Flips every Elyon env to the I2S parallel backend at once
- **Build matrix shrinks** from 10 envs to 8 (one per board, no duplicates)

---

## [2.20.1] — 2026-06-19

### Added
- **Orion setup wizard** — guided 5-step procedure (Mechanical → Direction → Run home → Travel limits → Profile sweep) with every control inline. Each step polls live state and ticks off when the operator completes the action. Re-runnable any time from the Calibration card; manual entry treats every step as "to redo"
- **Profile sweep auto-derives operSgthrs** — the operational StallGuard threshold is now computed automatically at the end of a successful 8-bin × 2-direction sweep (worst-case mean − 3·stddev). No separate calibration step needed
- **Auto-rehome on Clear Fault** — opt-in Orion Safety toggle: when the operator presses Clear Fault (UI button or DMX function byte 100-149) and the option is on, the fixture automatically starts homing after the fault is cleared. Operator stays in full control; no autonomous motion
- **DMX status badge** — header chip shows three states (DMX present / no DMX / OFFLINE) with green / yellow / grey colours
- **Per-universe DMX-loss watchdog** — fixtures can now arm their watchdog on a specific universe instead of "any DMX traffic"; Orion uses this so a silent motor universe still trips the return-home action while other universes keep playing

### Changed
- **Background.jpg** — recompressed from 141 KB to 25 KB (953×1200 progressive JPEG quality 72). First paint of the web UI is noticeably faster
- **Release artefacts** — `release/` is now organised per fixture: `release/veyron/v<ver>/`, `release/elyon/v<ver>/`, `release/orion/v<ver>/`
- **Manual jog "Override"** — now also suspends StallGuard stall detection, not just soft-limit enforcement. Lets the operator redefine travel limits without false stall trips when no profile is calibrated yet
- **Elyon render task** — LED rendering runs on a dedicated FreeRTOS task pinned to Core 0, woken by xTaskNotifyGive or a 20 ms safety tick. Frees the main loop on Core 1 from re-rendering on every iteration

### Fixed
- **Spurious restart on Save** — saving the configuration on Orion no longer schedules a restart when nothing actually changed
- **`generic_esp32_test_elyon_i2s` build** — missing I2SClocklessLedDriver dependency now declared in `platformio.ini`

---

## [2.20.0] — 2026-06-03

### Added
- **Clocked LED chipsets** — Elyon now supports APA102, SK9822 and P9813 in addition to the WS281x family. Clocked chipsets use two pins (data + clock); pick the partner output for CLOCK from a dropdown on the same card, and the partner output is marked as "Used as CLOCK" with its config greyed out
- **I2S parallel LED backend (opt-in)** — new `RAVLIGHT_MODULE_I2S_LED` build flag routes all WS281x outputs through a single I2S0 peripheral instead of one RMT channel per output. Lifts the per-output pixel cap from 500 to 1024 pixels; total pixel budget from 4096 to 8192. Default builds are unchanged (RMT). Contributed by Felix Trefou (@Lefix2)
- **Bring-up build** — new `env:generic_esp32_test_elyon` / `env:generic_esp32_test_elyon_i2s` builds for a plain ESP32-WROOM with no Ethernet or DMX controller; an internal walking-byte pattern drives every output at 40 fps so the signal path can be validated on a logic analyzer

### Changed
- **Web UI rendering** — the configuration page is now streamed in chunks as it is built, so it no longer truncates on devices with fragmented memory after long uptimes. Previously the page could stop mid-script, leaving the Save button and tab navigation broken until reboot
- **Elyon Relay** — new "Active-low (invert output)" toggle in the Relay section for relay modules wired active-low; the per-channel Brightness field is hidden when protocol is Relay since it has no effect there
- **WS2814 / WS2815 / TM1814 / TM1914 protocol options** added to the Elyon protocol dropdown

---

## [2.19.0] — 2026-05-29

### Added
- **Orion winch fixture (alpha)** — motorized winch control on the LED Lifter v5 board (TMC2209 stepper): DMX position and speed with three personalities, sensorless StallGuard homing, hold-to-jog manual control, a DMX-loss watchdog (E-stop or return-home), mechanical calibration (drum diameter / gear ratio / steps-per-rev → cm), soft travel limits, and a cm/inch unit selector
- **LED outputs on Orion** — Orion can drive WS281x LED strips alongside the motor; each output is configured independently (protocol, pixel count, universe, start channel, brightness, color order, grouping, invert) from a dedicated LED tab
- **StallGuard calibration wizard** — guided pop-up that tunes the stall threshold against the real hung load (no-load reading → loaded reading), with the result saved on the device
- **Per-output LED highlight** — a "Highlight" button on each LED output runs a white wipe along the strip to identify it (Elyon and Orion)
- **Tabbed configuration UI** — Network / DMX / Fixture / Settings are now tabs instead of stacked accordions; on Orion the fixture splits into separate Motor and LED tabs; each motor section is a collapsible card with a live summary

### Changed
- **RavLight logo** restored in the page header (previously plain text), on both the config page and the DMX Monitor
- **Header on phones** — runtime counters and board name are hidden on small screens to reduce clutter
- **DMX section** now explains that the Start Universe applies to the fixture's main block, while LED outputs use their own per-output universe

### Fixed
- **DMX Monitor universe selector showed "0 / NaN" on Orion** — the fixture channel map now uses the universe→ranges schema the monitor expects, so the selector lists the real universes and highlights fixture channels correctly

---

## [2.18.0] — 2026-05-12

### Added
- **QuinLED AN-Penta Plus board** — 7-channel board with Ethernet (LAN8720, ETH_CLOCK_GPIO17_OUT); CH1–5 analog PWM, CH6 digital level-shifted, CH7 relay; new `env:quinled_penta_plus_elyon`
- **QuinLED AN-Penta Deca board** — 15-channel all-PWM board (no Ethernet); CH1–8 use LEDC low-speed mode, CH9–15 use high-speed mode for a total of 15 simultaneous independent channels; new `env:quinled_penta_deca_elyon`
- **LED Relay protocol** — new output type in Elyon (`Relay`); reads one DMX channel and drives a GPIO HIGH/LOW based on a configurable threshold (default 128); threshold is editable per-channel in the UI; persisted as `"relay_thr"` in config JSON
- **Board-specific first-boot preset** — boards can define default output types applied automatically on first boot (NVS empty) and after factory reset; QuinLED Penta Plus defaults all outputs to PWM 1 kHz with CH7 as relay; QuinLED Penta Deca defaults all outputs to PWM 1 kHz
- **Elyon PWM invert** — new toggle inverts duty cycle for active-low LED drivers (DMX 0 → full duty, DMX 255 → off)

### Changed
- **Elyon output count follows hardware** — `ELYON_NUM_OUTPUTS` is now equal to `HW_LED_OUTPUT_COUNT` at compile time; boards with 2, 4, 7, 8, or 15 outputs get the exact right config array and UI row count
- **PWM channel assignment auto-derived** — `pwm_output_init` now accepts a flat channel index 0–15 and internally derives LEDC speed mode, channel, and timer; enables 15 independent PWM channels on Penta-Deca without manual config

---

## [2.17.0] — 2026-05-10

### Added
- **Elyon PWM — invert option** — new toggle in the PWM Dimmer section inverts the duty cycle (DMX 0 → full duty, DMX 255 → off); useful for active-low LED drivers; reflected correctly in `stopDMX` (inverted outputs go to full duty, not zero); persisted as `"pwm_inv"` in config JSON with zero-default backward compatibility

### Changed
- **Accordion animation** — open/close now animates smoothly using JS `scrollHeight` measurement; `max-height: none` is set after the opening transition so accordion contents can grow dynamically; all Elyon output cards start closed on page load
- **External CSS** — all embedded `<style>` blocks moved to `data/style.css`; `index.html` and `dmxmonitor.html` both link the shared file; `dmxmonitor.html` retains only page-specific overrides inline

---

## [2.16.0] — 2026-05-07

### Added
- **Gledopto Elite board support** — `boards/gledopto_elite_2d.h` (GL-C-616WL, 2 level-shifted LED outputs on GPIO 16+2) and `boards/gledopto_elite_4d.h` (GL-C-618WL, 4 outputs on GPIO 16,12,4,2); both use LAN8720 Ethernet with `ETH_CLOCK_GPIO0_IN`; new build environments `env:gledopto_elite2d_elyon` and `env:gledopto_elite4d_elyon`
- **Elyon UI row count follows hardware** — the outputs table now shows exactly `HW_LED_OUTPUT_COUNT` rows (compile-time constant injected as JS); boards with 2 or 4 outputs no longer show unused rows

### Changed
- **Unified fixture interface** — `include/fixture_webserver.h` declares four generic functions (`writeFixtureVars`, `injectFixturePlaceholders`, `handleFixtureSaveParams`, `registerFixtureRoutes`) implemented by each fixture; `include/fixture_config.h` extended with the DMX interface (`initFixture`, `handleDMX`, `startDMX`, `stopDMX`, `fixtureHighlight`); zero `#ifdef RAVLIGHT_FIXTURE_*` blocks remain in core code (`main.cpp`, `webserver_manager.cpp`, `discovery_udp.cpp`, `discovery_espnow.cpp`) — adding a new fixture requires only creating files under `src/fixtures/<name>/`
- **DimCurves moved to VeyronConfig** — dimming curve setting now lives in the `fixture` section of the config JSON, not in `dmx`; existing configs migrate transparently on load
- **Default DMX input changed to ArtNet** — new devices default to ArtNet instead of DMX Wired on factory reset

### Fixed
- **sACN not working on WiFi** — multicast group membership was bound to `INADDR_ANY` which resolves to the first interface (Ethernet) on dual-stack ESP32; membership is now bound to `netConfig.currentip`, which is updated on every network event via `reinitDMXInput()`; sACN works correctly when Ethernet is absent or disconnected
- **AUTO_SCENE option hidden on non-recorder builds** — the select option now carries `data-module="recorder"` and is hidden by the JS feature-flag system when `RAVLIGHT_MODULE_RECORDER` is not compiled in

---

## [2.15.0] — 2026-05-05

### Added
- **Device discovery — active module** — `RAVLIGHT_MODULE_DISCOVERY` now compiles a fully active discovery backend on any fixture; on-demand scan via UI "Devices" button sends UDP broadcast waves across a 4.5 s window; optional ESP-NOW scan adds support for devices not on the same subnet (AP-mode fixtures); scan results populate the devices table in real time

### Fixed
- **Asymmetric discovery** — Veyron could discover Elyon but Elyon could not discover Veyron; root cause was the RX socket (`s_rxUDP`) being reused for TX (`broadcastTo()`), which caused `udp_connect()` to leave a remote-address filter that silently dropped unicast replies; fixed by introducing a dedicated `s_txUDP` for broadcasting while `s_rxUDP` is kept strictly read-only

---

## [2.14.0] — 2026-05-05

### Added
- **Device discovery panel** — new "Devices" button in the action bar opens a panel listing all RavLight devices on the network; tap the info icon for details (ID, MAC, IP, firmware version, temperature, uptime); only visible when `RAVLIGHT_MODULE_DISCOVERY` is compiled in
- **Elyon Outputs — redesigned table** — each output now uses a two-row layout: row 1 shows Type, Pixels, Group (primary config); row 2 shows Order, Brightness, Universe, CH start (secondary/mapping fields); clearer visual separation between configuration and addressing

### Fixed
- **Elyon table disappears with large pixel counts** — `String::replace()` on ESP32 fails silently when the string needs more heap than pre-allocated; the Elyon HTML builder now pre-reserves capacity for all three replace steps (`rows`, `section`, `html`) before executing them; table renders correctly regardless of pixel count

---

## [2.13.0] — 2026-05-04

### Added
- **DMX Monitor** — live buffer visualization at `/dmxmonitor`; 32×16 grid shows all 512 channels with intensity color coding; fixture channels highlighted in yellow; universe selector auto-populated from fixture map; pause/resume toggle; Back link to main UI
- **Merged firmware binary** — post-build script combines bootloader, partitions, firmware and filesystem into a single flashable `release/<fixture>_<board>_v<version>.bin` (no multi-step flashing required); individual fw/fs binaries also exported to `release/`
- **Connection status badge** — Network accordion now shows active connection type (ETH / WiFi / AP-WiFi) in real time

### Changed
- **WiFi scan → datalist** — SSID field uses native `<datalist>` instead of a separate select; typing still works, scan results auto-open the suggestion list
- **Smart redirect after save** — when saving from AP mode, redirects to mDNS hostname; when on ETH or WiFi, redirects to the device IP

### Fixed
- **Factory reset kept static fixture ID** — `generateMacId()` is now called in every `loadDefaultConfig()` code path; device always gets a unique MAC-derived ID (e.g. `RVA1B2`) after reset
- **Elyon auto-layout overwrites saved addresses on page load** — `elyonAutoLayout` checkbox now starts unchecked; saved universe/channel values are preserved on page open
- **Elyon config download truncated at output 4** — `DynamicJsonDocument` pool was too small for 8 outputs; raised to 4096 bytes in all handlers and NVS save/load; all 8 outputs now round-trip correctly

---

## [2.12.0] — 2026-04-29

### Added
- **Multi-universe DMX pool** — `dmx_manager` now maintains a pool of up to 32 universes (`DMX_MAX_UNIVERSES`); fixtures call `registerDmxUniverse()` at startup and read live data via `getUniverseData()`; backward compatible (single-universe fixtures like Veyron unchanged)
- **Native ArtNet/sACN** — `hideakitai/ArtNet` and `ESPAsyncE131` libraries replaced with lwIP raw UDP sockets; ArtNet on port 6454 (`INADDR_ANY`) receives from all interfaces simultaneously (ETH, WiFi STA, AP); sACN on port 5568 joins a multicast group per universe — no consecutive-universe limitation
- **ArtPoll reply** — device responds to ArtPoll requests with a minimal ArtPollReply (short name, long name, universe, MAC) for automatic discovery by Resolume, GrandMA, etc.
- **ArtNet auto-reinit** — when Ethernet or WiFi connects (or AP starts), DMX inputs automatically reinitialise without device restart
- **Elyon multi-universe renderer** — each of the 8 outputs can span multiple universes; pixel-to-channel mapping uses flat channel index math across universe boundaries

### Fixed
- **Config save crash** (guru meditation) — NVS buffer was stack-allocated inside an AsyncWebServer callback (limited stack); moved to heap (`malloc`/`free`)
- **ArtNet crash with Ethernet disconnected** — `artnet.begin()` (EthernetUDP) fails silently when Ethernet is not up, leaving an internal null socket; `artnet.parse()` then dereferenced it; guarded with `ETH.linkUp()` check and `artnetReady` flag
- **SoftAP name** — access point was named with the MAC address placeholder; now uses `PROJECT_NAME-ID_fixture` format (e.g. `RavLight-A1B2`)

### Removed
- `hideakitai/ArtNet`, `ESPAsyncE131`, `arduino-libraries/Ethernet` library dependencies — replaced by native lwIP socket implementation

---

## [2.11.0] — 2026-04-28

### Added
- **QuinLED Dig-Octa Brainboard-32-8L support** — new board file `boards/quinled_octa.h`; 8 LED output GPIOs (0,1,2,3,4,5,12,13), LAN8720A Ethernet (ETH_CLOCK_GPIO17_OUT, no power pin)
- **Elyon fixture** — 8-output LED controller; each output independently configured with pixel count and DMX start address; personality selects 1/2/4/8 active outputs; all driven via IDF 4.4 RMT (`RMT_CHANNEL_0..7`, `mem_blocks=1`)
- **`env:quinled_octa_elyon`** — QuinLED Dig-Octa + Elyon build environment in `platformio.ini`
- **`RAVLIGHT_HAS_STATUS_LED`** capability flag — status LED `pinMode`/`digitalWrite` in `dmx_manager` now guarded; boards without a status LED compile cleanly

---

## [2.10.0] — 2026-04-28

### Added
- **Native LED drivers** — FastLED and NeoPixelBus removed; WS2811 strip now driven via ESP-IDF 4.4 RMT (`led_output_t`, `src/core/led_output.cpp`); P9813 accent pixels via GPIO bit-bang (`p9813_t`, `src/core/p9813.cpp`)
- **`led_output_t`** — generic RMT LED strip driver abstraction; one instance per channel; ready for Elyon (8 independent RMT channels)
- **`p9813_t`** — P9813 bit-bang driver; start/end frame protocol; no SPI library dependency

### Fixed
- **WS2811 white-glitch at low brightness** — the strip uses 800 kHz WS2812B-compatible protocol; the original 400 kHz T0H (500 ns) exceeded the strip's ~600 ns threshold and was read as `1` by every zero bit; corrected to T0H = 400 ns (clk_div=4, 50 ns/tick)

---

## [2.9.0] — 2026-04-27

### Added
- **LittleFS** replaces SPIFFS — better wear leveling and power-cut resilience; partition format migrates automatically on first boot
- **Config in NVS** — device configuration now stored in NVS blob (namespace `ravlight`), completely separate from the filesystem; uploading new web assets via `uploadfs` no longer wipes WiFi credentials and settings
- **DMX Recorder — complete** — records any DMX source (ArtNet, sACN, wired) into 4 slots at 40 fps for 10 s each; slot selection and active slot saved in config and survive restart
- **Auto Scene playback** — selecting *Auto Scene* as DMX source loops the chosen slot continuously without any separate play button; switching to another source stops playback immediately; changing slot mid-playback takes effect on the next Save without switching source
- **Recording feedback** — Web UI polls the device and shows a *Recording complete* notification when the 10 s capture finishes
- **IDF API migration (Fase 1)** — `runtime`, `config`, and `dmx_recorder` modules now use native ESP-IDF calls: `ESP_LOG*`, `esp_timer_get_time`, `esp_wifi_get_mac`, `gpio_set_direction`/`gpio_get_level`, `esp_restart`
- **`dmxBuffer` mutex** — protects concurrent access to the DMX buffer from network callbacks and the recorder task

### Changed
- `runtimeNVS` module renamed to `runtime`; NVS flash initialisation moved to `config` (primary NVS owner); runtime data in separate namespace `runtime`
- Config upload/download handlers rewritten to use in-memory struct serialisation instead of reading `/config.json` from filesystem
- DMX source dropdown order: ArtNet → sACN → DMX Wired → Auto Scene

### Fixed
- Accumulated runtime hours preserved across firmware upgrades via one-shot NVS namespace migration (`storage` → `runtime`)
- LED output was frozen during scene playback — the renderer was incorrectly gated by the same flag used to block live DMX input

---

## [2.8.0] — 2026-04-27

### Added
- **DMX patch list system** — semantic channel typing for fixture personalities: each output channel carries its type, section, default value, and count; enables fixture-agnostic rendering logic
- **Fixture webserver architecture** — Veyron-specific web routes, HTML injection and save parameter handling moved into `src/fixtures/veyron/`; shared web server code is now fixture-independent
- **Restart overlay** — when saving WiFi or network settings, a countdown overlay appears immediately and redirects automatically to the device mDNS address after 10 seconds
- **Axon and Elyon fixture headers** — skeleton personality tables for the ArtNet-to-RS485 bridge (Axon) and 8-output LED controller (Elyon)

### Changed
- Dimming Curve setting moved from general Settings into the Veyron Fixture accordion
- Scene Recorder moved from the Veyron Fixture accordion into the DMX accordion (it is a DMX module, not fixture-specific)

### Fixed
- Saving DMX address or personality no longer restarts the device — restart now only triggers when WiFi, IP or fixture ID actually change
- Device restart after network save now completes reliably (was dropping the HTTP response before transmitting it)

---

## [2.7.0] — 2026-04-24

### Added
- **Board file pattern** (`boards/`) — port RavLight to any ESP32 board by adding a single header file; no core code changes needed
- **`RAVLIGHT_MODULE_ETHERNET`** — Ethernet support is now an explicit compile-time flag; WiFi-only boards compile cleanly without it
- **Config JSON v2** — settings file restructured in named sections (`network`, `dmx`, `fixture`); auto-migrates from v1 on first boot
- **Board name in Web UI header** — shows which board is running at a glance

### Changed
- PlatformIO environment renamed `veyron` → `xdmx_v2_veyron` (board + fixture naming)
- DMX Recorder is in progress — record/playback not yet complete

### Fixed
- Dimming curve selection was off-by-one: Linear/Square/Inverse Square/S-Curve now map correctly to the Web UI dropdowns

---

